value.value: The muscle that inserts on the antenna.
The carina that is transverse and extends across the lateral wall of the terebra.
The pleurite that extends ventrally of the lateral margin of the tergum and dorsally of the coxopleurite.
The anatomical cluster that is composed of the strongly sclerotised areas corresponding with the annuli and less strongly sclerotised areas situated between them.
The articulation that is part of the second valvifer-second valvula-third valvula complex and adjacent to the rhachis.
The impression that arises just medially of the anterior tentorial pit and extends distomedially on the clypus delimiting laterally a triangular, convex area of the clypeus.
The projection that is located along the medial margin of the parossiculus.
The row of setae that extends along the ventral margin of the probasitarsus.

The anatomical cluster that is composed of longitudinal rows of spurs extending along the tarsomeres of the protarsus and are continuous with the row of spur of the preceeding and/or subsequent tarsomeres.
The anatomical cluster that is formed from the tarsal claw and the apical tarsomere, and is grasping in function.
The projection that is located on the distal margin of the clypeus.
The anatomical cluster composed of the apical flagellomeres that are differentiated by size from the basal flagellomeres.
The flagellomere that is located in the clava.
The carina that is longitudinal and is located on the clypeus.
The sulcus that corresponds to the clypeo-pleurostomal line.
The area that is located posteriorly on the second abdominal tergum and is delimited anteriorly by an impression.
The process that is located on the annulus.
The area that is located distally of the wing base.
The intrinsic leg muscle that arises ventrally from the protibia and inserts ventrally on the articular membrane of the protibio-probasitarsal joint.
The intrinsic leg muscle that arises anteriorly from the tibia and inserts ventrally on the proximal margin of the metabasitarsus.

label.value: ventral metapleuro-third axillary sclerite of hind wing muscle

value.value: The metapleuro-third axillary sclerite of hind wing muscle that arises ventrolaterally from the metapectus.
The intrinsic leg muscle that arises ventrally from the mesotibia and inserts ventrally on the articular membrane of the mesotibio-mesobasitarsal joint.
The unguitractor plate that is located on the protarsus.
The unguitractor plate that is located in the metatarsus.
The unguitractor plate that is located in the mesotarsus.
The anatomical structure that is located on the flagellomere, elongate, convex and its width is at least one fifth of the diameter of the flagellomere.
The fossa that is located laterally on the proximal margin of the profemur accommodating the femoral articular process of the protrochanter.
The fossa that is located laterally on the metafemur and accommodates the femoral articular process of the metatrochanter.
The fossa thet is located laterally on the proximal margin of the mesofemur.
The carina that delimits posteriorly the metepisternal depression.
The line of separation that extends along the transscutal line.

The line  that is longitudinal, extends ventrolaterally on the mesopleuron and corresponds with the site of origin of the second and third mesopleuro-third axillary sclerite of fore wing muscle and the second mesopleuro-mesonotal muscle.
The tibial fossa of the femur that is located on the protibia.
The fossa that is located distally on the femur and accommodates the femoral condyle of the tibia.
The condyle that is located on the tibial articular process of the probasitarsus and inserts into the basitarsal fossa of the protibia.
The condyle that is located on the tibial articular process of the metabasitarsus and inserts into the basitarsal fossa of the metatibia.
The condyle that is located on the tibial articular process of the mesobasitarsus.

label.value: tibial articular process of the probasitarsus

value.value: The articular process that is located dorsally on the proximal margin of the probasitarsus and bears the tibial condyle of the probasitarsus.

label.value: tibial articular process of the metabasitarsus

value.value: The articular process that is located dorsally on the proximal margin of the metabasitarsus and bears the tibial condyle of the metabasitarsus.

label.value: tibial articular process of the mesobasitarsus

value.value: The articular process that is located dorsally on the proximal margin of the mesobasitarsus and bears the tibial condyle of the mesobasitarsus.

label.value: third mesopleuro-third axillary sclerite of fore wing muscle

value.value: The fore wing third axillary muscle that originates posterolaterally from the mesopleuron.
The abdominal muscle that inserts on the abdominal tergum.
The metacoxal muscle that arises from the metanotum.
The area that is located on the epicnemial carina anteriorly of the site of origin of the omaulus.
The area that is located between the oral and the occipital foramina.
The projection that is located on the distal half of the tarsal claw and proximal to the apex.
The scrobe that is located ventrally of the antennal foramen and accommodates the proximal part of the antenna.
The carina that corresponds with the mesepimeral inflection and delimits the subalar area.
The anatomical cluster that is composed by transverse rows of setae on the median (posterior, inner) surface of the metabasitarsus.
The abdominal muscle that inserts on the abdominal sternum.
